## Required Output Format

Output the complete refined graph in XML:

```xml
<graph>
  <nodes>
    <node id="unique_id" type="claim">
      <text>Claim text</text>
      <sources>
        <source>source_id</source>
      </sources>
      <evidence>
        <quote source="source_id">Exact verbatim substring from source (must match character-for-character)</quote>
      </evidence>
    </node>
  </nodes>
  
  <edges>
    <edge id="unique_id" type="supports" from="node_id" to="node_id">
      <sources>
        <source>source_id</source>
      </sources>
    </edge>
  </edges>
</graph>
```

**XML Formatting Rules**:
1. Output MUST be valid XML within `<graph>` tags.
2. Node types: claim, evidence_quote, counterclaim, uncertainty.
3. Edge types: supports, attacks, refines, about, depends_on.
4. Ensure all tags are properly closed.

Include ALL nodes and edges (existing + new). Use consistent IDs.

